\displaystyle e^x+e^{-x} = \sum_n \frac{x^n}{n!} + \sum_n (-1)^n \frac{x^n}{n!} = 2\sum_{n \text{ even}} \frac{x^n}{n!} = 2 \sum_n \frac{(x^2)^n}{(2n)!} \leq 2 \sum_n \frac{(x^2)^n}{n!} = 2 e^{x^2}
 e^x=\sum_{n\geq 0}\frac{x^n}{n!}\quad \forall x\in\mathbb{R}. 
